snippet: Likely presidential candidates from the party’s establishment have indicated they will compete in Iowa, whose caucuses have long been dominated by conservatives and libertarians.
abstract: Iowa Republicans are looking forward to state's renewed clout in coming 2016 presidential elections, as national contenders like Jeb Bush and New Jersey Gov Chris Christie begin to lavish attention on state; Iowa's caucus suffered declining importance after it was won by conservative activists in 2008 and 2012, but Gov Terry E Branstad has since engineered purge that has again opened state's doors to mainstream candidates.
lead_paragraph: Likely presidential candidates from the party’s establishment have indicated they will compete in Iowa, whose caucuses have long been dominated by conservatives and libertarians.

headline.main: Iowa Republicans See Renewed National Clout
headline.print_headline: Iowa Republicans See Renewed National Clout
